longBusinessSummary: GreenBank Capital Inc., through its subsidiaries, invests in small cap businesses in North America. It operates through four segments: Merchant Banking, Financial Services, Software Development, and Mineral Exploration. The company provides private equity, public listings, small cap investments, corporate restructuring, merger and acquisitions, reverse mergers, and business incubating services, as well as transfer agency services. It also offers identification based blockchain and blockchain based medical confidentiality systems to the healthcare community, as well as digital information management systems for the cannabis industry. In addition, the company provides services to expatriates seeking to settle in Canada; and operates an online portal that offers dissemination of company news through press releases, research reports, and commentary. Further, it holds interests in the Twilite gold property comprising 65 claims located at southwest of Grand Falls-Windsor, Newfoundland; the Daniel's Harbour zinc mines that consists of 85 claims situated at the west coast of Newfoundland; the Browning property, which include 24 claims located at south of Pollards Point, Newfoundland; and the Cripple Creek property comprising 35 claims and the Duder Lake property that includes 8 contiguous claims situated in Gander, Newfoundland, as well as an option to acquire the Kapuskasing's Daniel's Harbour property comprising 42 claim units located in the western Newfoundland. The company also develops social media platforms and mobile application game, as well as acts as an insurance agent. GreenBank Capital Inc. was incorporated in 2013 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
